,Recommended,241560,20365698,"Posted: 6 January, 2016",all,BioVenom,"After around 40 hours of playing, I have completed the story, yet there is so much replayability since the map is amazing. But I will discuss what I think are the pros and cons and possible improvements of the game.Pros:- Loading Screens are replaced with cinematics and statistics/parts. Using an SSD, these load time seems very quick.- Huge World Size/Map, the large map with the amount of detail put in is incredible, each area feels representative and visually stunning. This by far is the best part of the game. You can even zoom right into the other side of the map, and see LIVE details. Even sitting on the opposite side of the world map.- AFK Cinematic, when AFK your screen goes into different camera angles around your vehicle, with the terrain and weather affecting it.- 5 Base Car specs, These being Street, Performance, Circuit, Dirt, and Raid. Each with their pros and cons. Myself I prefer Circuit and Performance. These specs determine where and how you drive. (Expansion adds Monster, Drift, Drag)- Day/Night Cycle. During the night, everything feels different, yet good. The night time scene can be as visually stunning as daytime.- Customization, the customization in parts, colours and stickers. Are very good. You can even customize your interior. This allows people to make their car look the way they like it for each spec.- Exploration, as there are so many places to go, plus the incentives like hidden car parts, and landmarks, it feels like you always have something to find. Plus you cannot FAST TRAVEL to places you haven't explored on the map.- Arcade-like, yet realistic. It is a fine line between the two, but The Crew seems to have found a nice balance. With destructible (yet respawnable) gameworld. Crashes are of course nowhere near as deadly, but damage to the car happens and is visible until repaired.- Factions, you can choose between 5 factions (eventually) each allowing you to represent them in faction races and events. Earn reputation and you can earn more in-game $$ too.- Coop/Friends - Playing with up to 4 friends is great, especially how every race/mission/skill has its own leaderboard. Competing against your friends score is a great incentive.- Price, I purchased The Crew whilst it was on Holiday Sale (50% off). so it felt very valued for the time spent. The retail cost seems fair, however. As there are at least 30 hours of missions. + Countless hours worth of skills/exploration/PVP/factions etc.- Public Transport, If you do not want to drive from New York to Discover Los Angeles (for example), you can take a train or airplane, as a sort of paid fast travel. But I recommend just driving.- Skills, along every route and dotted everywhere along the map, are skills. These are objectives to earn parts for your car and compete against your friend. Makes the trip more enjoyable when every 5-10 minutes you can do some weaving (Slalom) for some fun, and parts. (If you're good enough).- Police Chases, cause enough destruction around a surveyed area, and you get some police chasing after you. Get caught and pay a HEFTY fine.- Vehicle Stock. There are over 50 in-game purchasable cars, each able to be specced out in different ways, some being able to be specced in most areas.- Driver cam. Seeing the interior and the world as it would be, LOVE IT.Cons:- Cinematic Bugs, especially annoying since the cinematics are stunning. Having the audio completely drop out is really annoying. Even after replaying it at HQ, it still doesn't work. Having to replay the cinematic on youtube to hear it is not good. Also, a few times my car would flip over in the cinematic.- Locked to certain specs for races. I would like to compete against AI/friends using whatever car I want. But races will lock you to the SPEC. I think the route would balance what would be recommended vs what could be used.- Wild Run coaxing. Seems a bit pushy. Game starting screen, WILD RUN. Map spawn location. WILD RUN event. Certain skills (long jump etc) only achievable in drag car (WILD RUN). Want others to join you in missions (Look for crew) WILD RUN. I would like to see these features changed so that they less invasive, and more tempting rather than pushed you on. And for the price, Wild run is NOT worth it.- HQs / Tuners, most have the same background/area, some dingy commercial garage. Would like to see these being different and representative of the area.- Voice acting, it is not synced at all, and for some reason, they often call (Alex) 'kid'. Even if Alex is a middle-aged man. Pretty weird.- NO Cross Console compatibility. Cannot play with my console brethren.- PvP unbalanced. Vsing People 500pts above you. Lambo vs Mini Cooper.. Come on.- Perks should be removed completely, add the bonuses as standard when unlocking your allies.- 'Dumb' Smart Loot. Lvl 50 in a 600 pt car gets the highest score, better give him a bronze Lvl 25 part?? A lower score would have given me a better part.- Notifications on Old Parts. Seeing I have a new Lvl 25 bronze part for my platinum specced car when I visit the workshop is a bit annoying.Improvements:- Public Transport. Allowing the player to BOARD a train, or AIRPLANE, and visually see the map around them as they journey across.- Missions. Missions/Faction Races could be improved to be more rewarding. The 4hour race should have a way better reward then the 2.5hour race. A bigger REP or $$ Bonus would be nice. Also more of them. It is really simple to make them as the map is perfect. Just put a marker from A to B anywhere on the map.- Character Customization. Customization of 'Alex' would be great especially in the open multiplayer world. The Same change of clothes the whole game, does this guy even shower?- Music/Radio. More stations/music lists. It seems they are repeating quite frequently.- Test Drives. These should be like a normal test drive, drive wherever you want. Pay for damages. I do not like being limited to the small area (test lap) around the city the dealer is in. I would like to go to the track to be able to dry these cars out etc. There could be a % BOND of the Car Price that you have to pay before getting to drive it, and if you damage the car you end up paying for it later, like those A >  B missions that penalize car damage.- Car Specs. Having cars limited to 1 or 2 specs is not realistic. As most Perf cars could be Circuit cars and visa versa. Also, these should be visible to see what it would look like BEFORE purchasing.- Cross platform. Cross Console compatibility.- Removal of spec specific races. Or adding races that you can choose. Prefer the later option.- Random Vehicle Customization at DEALERS. Having it on purchased parts at the HQ is good, but being able to randomize what the car could look like at the tuner would be ideal.- Customization Lock options. Like the colour/shape (for example), should be able to lock those options.- AFK Cam, Toggleable On/Off and a smoother, slower shift in camera angles, over the Jumpy random camera angles. Also removal of the BLUR effect when in this mode.- Removal of 'Updating Content' loading. When alt-tabbing. Especially in borderless mode.- Controls. WASD STANDARD for speed etc. Who the hell uses arrow keys? Having everything on 1 side is easier. Lucky you can rebind them.- Scrapping Parts. Should be a lot more rewarding, and possible in the workshop.- Ragdoll effects on animals and people. If you hit them, you should probably see them go flying, instead of clipping through the car. A solid quick vibration would be a nice touch, for the real immersion.ConclusionAs usual, there are a lot of things that could be improved,.but I do highly recommend this game. Not only for racing, but for exploration.(If you found this review helpful, give it a thumbs up!)"
