76561198115301175,Recommended,241560,13595656,"Posted: 25 December, 2014",all,Calibreus,"I don't fully understand why there are so many bad reviews both on Steam and on the web... There are a lot of great things about this game and it really is next-gen with both it's graphics and absolutely fantastic open-world. Instead of writing a long and strenuous paragraph however; I will simply provide the pro's and con's of this game.Pro's:-Insane Open World (largest I have ever experienced in video game)-Beautiful Graphics (despite what others have said, when you crank this thing to ultra it sure is a beauty)-Good Handling/Physics (change the in-game handling in the settings to ""sport"" or ""hardcore"")-Beautiful Cars (they look basically the same as they do realistically)-Selection of Music (different radio stations that you can choose in-game while driving are really cool)-An Alive World (you'll see trains, planes, cars, pedestrians, trucks, law enforcement, et cetera anywhere you go)-Difficulty (it isn't a little kids game you can easily beat; it does take some skill)-Attention to Detail (there are abandoned houses in deserts that each look totally different, cops have different accents according to the state their in, landmarks can be found throughout the map and provide you with real-life facts about those destinations, et cetera)-Decent Story (it has a story and that's what counts in my opinion, it isn't amazing but it doesn't suck either)-Car Spec's (they are very cool and unlike what most people say; you do feel a difference between them)-Only Next-Gen Racing Game Available on PC (as of my knowledge, there are no other racing games on the PC that were released at the same time as the Crew. All of the Crew's competition like Forza Horizon 2 or Driveclub are only limited to the consoles at the moment)Con's-Some Buggy A.I. (especially in cop chases!)-Not A Huge Selection of Cars (I don't fully know how to explain it, but I feel there should just be a more varied selection of cars)-No Profanity Settings (I know I'm getting a little ridiculous here but it would be nice to have an option to bleep out the swears)-Not the Customization I was Expecting (it's not horrible but there just aren't that many customization options)-Pathetic Community (I have tried many times to do a proper co-op race with random players and it always fails because no one will join. I have also been bombarded by trolls that are hacking in high spec'd cars that do not meet there driver level at all)-Always Online (this hasn't affected me a ton but it's a bit irritating and can get a little laggy with a lot of players)-Crashes (due to the always online part; I have crashed a few times. Fortunately the game always saves my progress so it hasn't affected me yet)-DLC (although it won't really matter whether you get it or not in the campaign, I could see there being Pay2Win's in PvP. Like seriously Ubisoft, don't make people spend $60 on a brand new game just to be greeted by the stupid $25 DLC Season Pass)Summary:Should you buy this game? Well, if you love racing games and you love exploration and you have a beasty rig (that meets the recommended settings or even the minimum settings) then buy this game, It is fantastic.If you don't have what I mentioned but are still contemplating purchasing the game, it might be best to wait until the price goes down; $60 is expensive.Anyway, if you read this entire review and found it to be helpful; then thank you for your support! Hopefully it did help you to make a decision. ^.^"
