tysThe Crew offers a veeery big world to explore. To get from the west to the eastcoast you are driving something like 2-3 hours if you are fast. Also you got additional to the Storyraces and PvPstuff a tons of tests/skill mini missions where you can test your skills in some small disciplins. Escape fast, drive fast on a road, climb a hill and so on. If you want to get through everything you are going to have some 100 hours.In addition The Crew offers a very good Tuning system. Optic tuning is back in business in a little bit smaller version of the ""Need for Speed Underground 2"" tuning possibilitys. Front, Back, Enginecover, Side, inside the car, outside the car, vinyls and weels. You can change many things in the optic again which is a must have for racing games in my opinion.The powertuning is a little bit different. You get stuff after completing Missions and Skilltests. The bigger the level and the better you are, the better the stuff will be you are adding to your car. Later on you can get ""Platinum-Rank"" in every mission and skilltest which offers good stuff for your car in every skilltest and mission, the lowlevel ones and the highlevel ones.There is a good variation of cars in this game, however i miss a little bit the cheap streetcars like in the beginning of Underground 2 which you had to tune from zero to hero. You start with a little bit besser ""level"" of cars. You can find tiles and build secret cars and you can buy cars from the carstores. In the end you will have a variation of something like 40-50 cars i guess.Big world, finally good tuning, many missions and extras. Its a racing game we waited for years to release.10 / 10Server OnlinetimeSadly its an only online racing game which palys on a big Ubisoft server. (Or some servers, i dont know, you cant choose). You will put together with players in one session who are your ubisoft friends and who are on the same story-progression like you are.So you will see allways your friends and possible helpers for your mission.Servers are very stable in my eye. However, some disconnects happened to be true, but these didnt happen very often and i could play most of the time.9 / 10Total GradeIf we put everything together and a little bit of my personal grad we will get this grade which is in my eye a true one. Pls dont forget to Comment if you have another opinion or want to add something :)9 / 10[/b]- Evilemerold"
