76561198011237320,Recommended,241560,33025094,Posted: 29 June,all,CodeFox,"I only have 6h so far, so I cannot say much but I would like to share a little.TIP: For the BLACK SCREEN BUG - go to your ""my documents"" folder and look the ""The Crew"" folder. Inside it, you will find a file called ""PCScalability.xml"". Open it up with notepad, and look up for a line that contains the word "" Appearance= "". Now, after the equals sign, you will have a number (usually 2) and all you have to do is, change it to 1 and save the file.What this does is change the game from fullscreen mode into fullscreen borderless mode. I hope it helps.Now for the review. Actually its more like a tiny story, but for me it tells a lot about the game and what it is about. But before all, mind that this game is NOT A SIM. In a scale of 1 (arcade) to 10 (sim) I would say 3.5/10.I was driving around, trying to reach one of the missions on the map, then I got a call to support a package delivery (help someone to transport a package from point A to B, blocking cops along the way). I was like: allright, bring it! And all the suddend I found myself jumping from NY to LA in the middle of a crazy car chase. A few minutes later it was all over, the package was secure. Then I had to get back on track with my missions, and I was on the other side of the country. We always have the option to fast travel into places we've already visited, OR drive all the way. Instinctively I opened my map and started clicking for a fast travel. But then I realized: ""That's not what it's all about. That's how I drive in other games, not this one."" I grabbed the ultimate edition of the game and it comes with one of my favorite cars ever built the Nissan Fairlady Z. It was around 9pm in game when I started it, my tip back to NY and I drove that car in cockpit view for the most if the trip. I went thought the beautiful nevada desert, some snowy parts I have no idea where (I'm not from US sorry folks), and it was an extemely enjoyable 45min trip. Just me, my Z240, the night sky and some nice trip music.Pros:-Quite enjoyable driving.-Tons of cars, with cockpit view.-Tons of car kits that change the whole driving model of your car.-Bikes!-Amazing scenery!-Awesome interface (I like it)-Nice police chases.-Seamless transition to join other player's match or persuit.-Tons of micro events that you take part on the fly.-Tons of hidden stuff to find.Cons:-Netcode can be problematic sometimes hahah.-Crash psysics are a little inconsistent, sometimes crashing feels like hitting a wall of butter the car just slides off. Others you hit some invisible walls (only in very rare occations though).-Controls -keyboard- can be a little rough, sometimes I have problems to make small adjustments and keep a straight line, making the car feel unstable.-Drift is not as enjoyable and overly simplistic. It feels like your actual speed is dictated direcly by what gear you are (it feels clearly faster even though the indicated speed remains about the same).-Drag is the same story, I missed a bit of the sim mechanics for tunning.Wishes:-More old school Rock music for long travels.-More prominent engine sound.If I would recommend it? Damn right I do!"
