,Recommended,241560,13580447,"Posted: 24 December, 2014",all,Kita,"Edited for Wild Run and patches:Brief:Seamless cross-country racingGreat driving physicsDecent graphicsBeautiful interior details on every carWide system requirementsExcellent wheel and controller supportJapanese voice track makes the terrible story bearable -- The main character is voiced by the same actor as Keisuke Takahashi from Initial D.Very stable, with some minor bugs -- 4K resolution Camera Mode tends to crash the game or forget shaders during rendering.Could almost outcomfy Euro Truck Simulator 2, if there wasn't such a heavy emphasis on driving full speed all the time.Motorcycles just got a physics update, giving them more realistic handling and the ability for dirtbikes to do big powerslides and scrub off jumps, now taking just as much skill to drive fast as the cars. This increases the fun quotient of driving a bike, but makes it harder to compete against an equally-tuned car.Addendum:The whole point is to hit level cap and grind PVP or faction missions with friends, the early game is extremely tedious and limits the amount of connectivity the player has. The first couple of hours in Freeride and you'll see AI driving around in place of real humans. After you get to level 2 or so, they disappear and are replaced with humans, but only if your NAT is good.This game uses a console-style system to deal with multiplayer, so if your home network is not properly set up, you will find it to be a completely dead game, which it very much isn't.You are also kept from accessing your Season Pass bonus cars until after you reach  Level 10. I would have liked to complete the tutorial with the Cadillac Eldorado, but it will be a couple hours of gameplay before you can even touch those vehicles.Base controller settings are garbage -- Make sure to mess with the options to make driving comfortable. Primarily, the speed sensitivity should be turned down, and if you have a newer controller, turn the deadzone off.Not much content - that said, it is a RACING game, and it has all kinds of that. PVP now has multiple gametypes, and the car selection is much better than at release.Some promised features still not yet in gameSTILL NO REAR-VIEW MIRRORS IN COCKPIT VIEWAbsolutely cringeworthy plot no matter what language you listen to it in.tl;dr: Ridiculous fun with friends if you can stomach the kusoge elements, overbearing and far too long tutorial, and odd glitch. There simply isn't anything like it."
