76561198071270190,Recommended,241560,18943003,"Posted: 7 November, 2015",all,DeltaZ3r0,"The Crew ReviewWARNING: My opinions are just opinions, nothing more. Do not just buy this game because I said so, look at it overall and ask yourself if you want it.Side NoteA lot of people are saying that they keep getting disconnected from Ubisoft servers because of Ubisoft. They are lying. Ubisoft have fixed most, if not all connection bugs on their side. It is just their internet, if you have a solid internet connection, you will be able to play with hardly any interruptions at all.SummaryThe Crew is an open world MMO for racing. Sounds familiar, no? If you liked Test Drive Unlimited, you will most hopefully like this. It has a variety of cars, and what with a few DLC's and the new expansion pack 'Wild Run' coming out (more on that later) soon enough, this game will have you playing for quite a few hours either racing through the story, or taking a leisurely cruise through the Mountain States.Features- 30+ cars- 5 regions: each different from one another.- 5 different specifications: Street, Dirt, Performance, Raid, Circuit, 3 to be added: Drift, Monster and Dragster.- Short story, so you can get down to the pure racing and cruising- 8 player sessions, 9/10 times you are paired with your friend's session.- Lots of ways to make money.- Game will look beautiful, thanks to the new overhaul made by the Wild Run (17 November)ConsSome parts of this game can be enough to put some people off. For example, if you're looking for a deep storyline, MASSIVE amounts of players to mess around with and races with great AI, this game is not for you. However, lets face it. 32 cars all driving around in the same vicinity would take a beating on your PC (unless you have around 2 grand to play with). Also, this game will force uPlay on you. Not necessarily bad, just thought I should point that out. (Some people HATE uPlay).TL:DRLong story short, don't let people tell you its bad and then never play it. That's what the demo is for. Play the demo, see if you like it, and if you do, then go ahead, buy it and have fun. Think of this game as a successor to Test Drive Unlimited. After all, it was designed by the same people.Rating9/10★★★★★★★★★"
76561197983740996,Recommended,241560,17419918,"Posted: 6 August, 2015",all,Chane,"There are some reasons to dislike 'The Crew' but one that makes the game a recommendation – it's fun.Pros:- Enormous map of the U.S.A.- Very interesting, long campaign, almost like a movie. IMO best story ever in a racing game. 65 Missions- Some extremely long races. 2.5 hours from Miami to Los Angeles via New York!!!(Perfect to turn your head off after a long day at the office)- Nice graphics (if you find the right settings)- Many ways to improve your cars.- Cars can be tuned into street, off-road, performance, race or rally cars.(some cars can only be tuned into some of the types)- Visual tuning- Performance tuning- Co-op missions- Cockpit view- Different radio stations- Country side looks fantastic (cities not always)- Total open world, also in all races- All cars feel different- Police (but too easy to escape)- Tons of mini games- All kind of animals, the crocodiles in the New Orleans swamps look fantastic- day/night cycle- addictiveCons:- Frame-rate sometimes drops, especially in cities. Changing graphic settings does not prevent this.- Car handling isn't the best in the beginning of the game but gets better after improving individual car settings- Very hard to make money, but you need money to buy cars. After 40 hours of playing I only have like 10 cars. There are about 50 cars in the game but you have to consider the different race-types (race, rally, etc.) So you can have like 200 different cars if you have the money. (not all cars support all types)- You can buy game money with real money :-(((- Some cars can only be bought with real money :-(((...but you do not need them to win in MP- Permanent on-line connection required- Game takes long to start- Upgrading cars is time consuming and can be frustrating. Every car can be upgraded to max level 1299. You need to play tests (hill climb, slalom, speed test, escape, etc.) to collect upgrade kits. But the game randomly decides which upgrade level you will receive. So even if you successfully complete the test you might not get the upgrade part you need. If you attempt to upgrade a car that already has a high level you can repeat tests like 50 times without being granted with the missing part, although you succeeded the test 50 times. Alternatively you can buy missing car parts but only if you have already earned the desired upgrade level and the fact that the game keeps you low on money makes upgrading by buying parts a painful decision.- MP race selection can be frustrating. Before each mp event every player can select their favorite event. Players can select the track, the car type and mp event type (racing, king of the crown, etc.). They can decide to activate or deactivate contact with other players and activate or deactivate traffic. A random selection carried out by the game will decide who's player selection will be played next.- High influence of luck in MP if you play with crash kids. You can lead 90% of a race but if someone pushes you into a field at 300 kph you're almost certain to become last. IMO it's best to select races with deactivated player contact but it's a matter of luck if you will play such race or not because the game decides which event is going to be played.- AI is too easy most of the time- Not a MMO. Eight simultaneous players in free drive mode- No rain, no snow, no weather conditions- Uplay- If Ubisoft servers are unavailable you can not play.- Sometimes mp players seem to cheat, but very rarely.'The Crew' is not a serious racing game like 'Dirt', 'Grid' or 'Project Cars'. It's an arcade fun racer in a cozy, feel good world that simply looks fantastic. The star of the game is the enormous and beautiful U.S.A. and the story."
