,Recommended,241560,17192463,"Posted: 23 July, 2015",all,zbig,"Before I tried this game I have read all the negative reviews and was very sceptical.Its great that they made a trial version of the game, so everyone can test it. I highly recommend it.First of all the game runs very smoothly on my gaming notebook (3 Years old now) of which I was very surprised, as its a great leap forward comparing to Test Drive Unlimited.The world is huge and the game is technicaly on a high level of detail.First negative that stroke me and that other reviewers were writing about was the bad driving physics. The cars slide a lot that is true. I blamed the keyboard controls for that, then I have connected my G25 racing wheel and the default settings were way off. I really wanted to uninstall the game on the spot but I have made some research and found a good configuration for the wheel and I must say that the game imiedately became playable and enjoyable.So if you have a wheel and are willing to play with the configuration you will get a nice experience, well I did. You should not expect the driving model of Project Cars, but there is so much to expolore in this game and I like many new ideas they have brought up.It is a shame that because of bad defaults such a huge game leaves a bad taste. This game could benefit from more players become even more enjoyable. The quick way to team up with others is IMHO nicely implamented in the game.Final verdict:Give it a trial ! Just spend a moment configuring your controls."
