76561197961171584,Recommended,241560,20460705,"Posted: 10 January, 2016",all,K31TH3R,"Here's everything I wish people would've told me about this game while I debated buying it, summarized from most to least important:-From a complete simulator geek obsessed with race sims, on hardcore mode with a Logitech G27, the physics lean much more towards simcade than arcade. In fact, the physics remind me a lot of Gran Turismo 4, with much better low speed differential physics (aka you can actually do a proper donut)-The vehicle upgrades can be used to vastly impact vehicle handling, and if the car feels unrealistic, swapping around differential parts and tires makes a huge difference, and can make an upgraded car that feels arcade-y, to VERY sim feeling.-If you own a Logitech G27 and you don't own this game, WHAT ARE YOU DOING WITH YOUR LIFE?-It's the TRUE spiritual successor to Test Drive Unlimited, and you should forget TDU2 ever existed.-While the graphics resembles TDU2 (same lead environment artist, who is now employed by Rockstar) NOTHING ELSE DOES, SO FEAR NOT, that POS game can be forgotten and/or nuked into eternity.-The developers who created this game LOVED it, and it shows.Tips:-If you have a low end processor, turn geometry settings down. The visual impact is minimal (a little more pop in) and it will vastly boost your FPS-If you have a low end GPU, turn Ambient Occlusion to SSAO or off.-If you love race sims, have a wheel, you NEED to buy this game. PERIOD."
