76561198166166320,Recommended,241560,24024044,"Posted: 2 July, 2016",all,EpicJustin1,"NOTE: At the time of writing this review, I have completed 36 hours so far.I just want to say, first off - I would take this over ANY and EVERY Need for Speed game out there. Yeah, that's right EA. I am an ex-customer of your company.Ok, so The Crew is that kind of game where once you start playing it, and after you're done playing it for the day, you really don't want to play any other game. At least that's how it is for me. And yes, it is my favorite game and I feel like it will stay that way for a LONG time. It has tons of cars in it, it has a HUMONGOUS map, and it has a good storyline (for an arcade-style game).First, the best part: the ""minimum"" system requirements can definitely go some lower than they are currently. Guess what my graphics card is? Ok, get ready... Intel HD Graphics Family. Yeah. BUT - on the lowest possible game settings - it runs The Crew pretty well! I was SHOCKED when I tried the Demo, before I got the complete edition, that it didn't lag crazily or didn't crash or give error messages. Also I'm on Windows 10 and my computer is a laptop, just worth noting. Also, if you're that kind of gamer that HAS to have the game on highest, most luxurious settings, and you have a non-gaming computer, then you pretty much are forced to lower your settings in-game. Come on, be grateful that the game is at least playable on whatever computer you have. HOWEVER, don't take what I'm saying here and apply it to all computers. I'm talking about an Intel HD Graphics Family specifically, I have absolutely NO idea what lesser computers will be like with this game. Just putting that out there.Ok, now moving on to the (few) bad things. Firstly, I am not too sure if this is my computer's fault, or the game, or Steam, or what - but every once in a while I will start the game, go into free-roam, and the car will automatically go forward OR sometimes backwards. I will attempt to stop it, by pushing either control, does nothing... and even when I go Ctrl-Alt-Delete, it does it THERE too! It selects things in either an upwards or downwards motion, and the only thing I know to do is restart the dang computer. This is very frustrating, and I don't exactly know how to fix it, I've gone to Google, no close-enough results show up there. Hopefully someone high-ranked can fix it though. Next, a minor inconvenience, whenever you crash into something with your car, it creates white lines all over the area of impact. Kind of wierd, but... it's not a simulator, so I'll let that one pass. That's just about everything I don't like that I can think of right now, I'm currently at level 26 so if I find anything else later on in The Crew, I'll edit this review. Hope this informed some people about certain stuff. Thanks for reading!"
