,Recommended,241560,18420081,"Posted: 10 October, 2015",all,utopian,"The Crew has it issues like sudden crashes (but that’s expected being a UBISOFT PC game) but even then they don't happen often, but what really bugs me is how you can be free driving and all of a sudden you run through a mini-game challenge, sometimes you can simply swerve out of the way but on small road with guard rails it’s impossible not to go through them, you then have to click ESC and abort it which completely ruins the experience. Now they can be helpful for gaining parts and XP but it would be nice if you could avoid them. I think my only other big issue in this game is if you get in close proximity to an item (im guessing a collectible to get the hidden car) the radar starts this infernal bleeping noise that will not stop unless you drive away. I also have some smaller issues with the gameplay being that although they saved us from tailing and time missions in ACU they just couldn’t help adding some off road tailing and takedown missions which I might add are really hard to do due to the weird off road physics that if you go over a bump your truck goes vertical and when it lands it swerves. Also I know it’s a racing game but I can’t help but feel they could have put a bit more diversity in the missions. Some good points are for the most parts the physics are good, the driving is also very responsive and it feels good to take turns and show off, the graphics are stunning, the car selection is decent and the joy I receive from just driving around and exploring the huge map really makes the game for me. And although there are micro-transactions thankfully they are not vital to completing the game. Last thing I’ll say is that you don’t have to join an online crew with real people or play the missions with other players, it can be played completely single player, I’m sure this is well known but at the time I purchased the game I didn’t know and the information would have been helpful in my decision. So I think at the core like all UBISOFT games it’s a really good game and defiantly worth paying, especially if you’re into open world racing."
