76561197968067067,Recommended,241560,18504774,"Posted: 16 October, 2015",all,Smeg,"You catch a guy by going around in circles, a nitro that makes your car go slower and I got an acheivement for going 250mph in a car with a top speed of 150mph. Would play again."
,Recommended,241560,18547810,"Posted: 18 October, 2015",all,Zardoz93,"Ahh... The Crew. I must say, this is probably the best racing game I have ever played. Yes, I do have experience with racing games, as I have played NFS:UG, NFS:HP, Forza 4, Forza Horizon 2, GT, and GT5. However, I have never had more fun on a racing game than I have had playing The Crew. The Crew features a HUGE open world MMO (and by huge, I mean that it's literally a condensed version of the United States). The map has 5 major regions: the Midwest, the East Coast, the South, the Mountain States, and the West Coast. Each region has it's own main city, except for the Midwest, which has two. The Midwest has Detroit and Chicago, the East Coast has NYC, the South has Miami, the Mountain States has Las Vegas, and the West Coast has Los Angelas. Each region  has it's own smaller states too, such as Salt Lake City from the Mountain States, and Sacremento from the West Coast. The map is so big I probably haven't even explored 75% of it yet.There is a pretty large selection of cars to choose from, from a Ford GT to a Nissan Skyline R34, and each have at least one out of five specs (the starter cars have all specs, and so do some other cars). The specs are: Street, Dirt, Performance, Raid (which is basically almost monster level), and Circuit. Street is the middle child when it comes to speed, but it handles great and can take corners easily. The best car for Street is probably the Nissan Skyline R34. Dirt is for slight off-roading, as it is very fast on dirt and road, but can still go offroad faster than Street, but not much faster. The best car for Dirt is porbably the Ford Focus RS. Performance is the second fastest, and is the one you'll probably race with the most during the story. It take corners well, but not as well as Street, but it's speed makes up for it. The best Perf car is probably the Koenigsegg Agera R, Ferrari LaFerrari, or Lamborghini Aventador. Raid is for straight-up offroad and taking people out. It's the slowest, but it doesn't need a road to get to one's destination. It is the fastest offroad. The best Raid car is probably either the Chevrolet Silverado or the Ford Raptor. Now for Circuit. Circuit destroys on roads, hands down, but when it comes to offroad, you're better off just fast-traveling to the nearest street. The best Circuit is probably the Ford GT or Saleen S7.The story is great. I had a lot of fun playing it. Play as Alex Taylor, who was put in prison for being framed for the murder of his own beloved brother, Dayton, by a V2 from the 5-10s named Shiv, and a corrupt police officer named Coburn. Travel across the U.S.A. to climb to the top of the 5-10s to get revenge on Shiv.All in all, this is a great game. I don't think I can stress how much I loved it."
