,Recommended,241560,24091083,"Posted: 4 July, 2016",all,Aids McGuff,"This is a fantastic game, if you like arcade racing. I almost didn't purchase the game because of negative reviews, but with a friend of mine saying how good it was, I thought I'd try it. I don't know how the game was in the past, but it is a great arcade racing game not unlike the Midnight Club series.The game has a lot of content and I have only scratched the surface so far. The controls are great and there's a lot of performance and visual customization for most of the cars. There is a lot of tuning options for how car responds to the controls, whether it be gamepad, wheel, or mouse/kb. There's many events, the map is huge, and the gameplay is extremely fun. If you've been wanting a Midnight Club for PC, like me, this surpassed even my expectations.The only negative things so far is that the story isn't that great (but I really don't play racing games for story), and that the menus for shops are pretty slow since you have to wait for an animation to play between most of the options. Despite the menu issue, I really think it's a solid game and the mmo is a nice touch, even though you can only see a few people around you at a time, there's a lot of options to  connect with people via events and crews.If you only like sim games, I wouldn't recommend this unless perhaps you tune your car a certain way. Otherwise this one of the best arcade racing games for PC at the moment."
