,Recommended,241560,22114340,"Posted: 28 March, 2016",all,Sir Jonthen,"If I could give this game a totally mixed review, I would. I have therefore decided to recommend this game, but only when it's on sale half price, like when I got it.In my experience, the story is forgettable, the missions can get repetitive (and often very difficult) and the 'RPG elements' including car upgrades are severely lacking. I would have loved to see actual individual upgrade purchases, like in the forza games, rather than meaningless stats. I completed the story missions in around 20 hours, playing entirely single player (the game includes worryingly few other players btw), which is feel is a more than acceptable gameplay time.The thing that redeems the game though (mostly) is the map and the cars... Firstly, i'll talk about the map. Ignore all of the criticism of it being too small, or not very detailed, its amazing. There are enough areas to carry on exploring after the story is completed and driving around is very fun on its own! If free roaming is your thing, then you will love this. The cars, as i've mentioned before, have limited customization when it comes to performance, which is a shame. HOWEVER, you can customize the looks of your cars, from decals, to alloys, to bumpers as much as you want. Also, you can customize a car for each spec you have it tuned to, so effectivley having multiple versions of each car! You can build your favourite cars and then use the in-game photography mode (which is very in-depth) to take pictures wherever you want, with filters, lighting, weather effects etc. This part of the game, however small, can eat up hours if you like getting the perfect screenshot!Overall, this game is somewhat disappointing, when you consider the marketing and what it claims to be.. a driving MMO! If you want a simulation game, or something with hardcore racing, it's definatley not for you. If however, you are a fan of more 'arcadey' racing games, or just want something different to play, I would give it a try. I wouldn't however say it's worth the full price, especially when its plagued with DLC and microtransactions!"
