,Recommended,241560,13214267,"Posted: 3 December, 2014",all,Rockerbacon,"Game is really fun. If you like arcade racing games it is a must have.Pros:-The way the car drives is pretty customizable and even though you can't make huge changes like making it a sim, you can definitely make it drive to your taste (as long as you enjoy arcade driving).-Game creates the perfect challange. You can win most races with relative ease, but getting that gold medal definitely requires some skill.-People have been bashing the graphics, but for an online-focused open world racing game the graphics are really impressive.-Online experience seems pretty stable. One problem I always have with online racing games is how crazy things go when playing online, cars popping out of nowhere, suddenly stoping or accelarating, etc. So far I have experienced no major problems while playing coop events.-Variety of car classes and events for those classes. There are car classes build for different terrains and conditions and events for those different classes.-Don't like playing with other people? You can go completely solo. Even though the game is online-focused you can ignore everyone around you and play it like if it was a singleplayer game.-Even though it's an arcade game you can feel the differences in handling of each vehicle with ease, making car choices come to preference.-That huge map! Travelling from one city to another is already a lot of fun and there are kind of mini-games in every road that include jumping, slaloms, driving fast and on the road, etc. All to keep you busy on your travels while also rewarding you.-The performance is flawless. Some people may be worried about performance since it's a Ubisoft game, but I have a pretty old computer and can still run the game flawlessly with mixed high/ultra settings.Neutral:-There are not many visual customization options as I though there would be, but customizing your car is still pretty fun, even though I feel it could be better.-Soundtrack doesn't fit the game well. The songs don't give you that adrenaline that make you want to drive fast and recklessly. But I believe no one cares for game soundtracks anymore, since most people just mute the game music and use an external music player.-The story feels kinda dull. The story is amazing the first minutes of gameplay, but once you hit the road it doesn't feel like a big deal anymore, but all online-focused games are like this. I haven't completed the game yet, so take this one with a grain of salt.-Cops are lazy. You have to do some real♥♥♥♥♥♥for them to go after you, just driving a clearly illegaly modified car 100Km/h above speed limit won't do it. Some people will love it, some others will hate it. Sometimes they also appear during races and don't do anything. In events where they're the main deal it's a different story, of course.Cons:-The car sounds are pretty bad, they just don't sound reallistic. Sometimes I feel like hearing an engine that came from a 2005 game.-You win performance parts in every event, which completely makes the performance shop useless allowing you to make a lot of money very easily since you have to spend very little of it to progress through the game. Remember that I haven't completed the game yet, it may change at some point.-You can't play the game offline, as far as I know. People who don't have access to a decent connection all the time must be very careful when buying this game.Some people have been saying this game is horrible, it is not. I haven't experienced bugs, lags, freezes, ctds or anything like that. The game is just great, even though it's not amazing. It's a great game that will give you a lot of fun specially if you play with your friends, but there's nothing really groundbraking about it.Also, don't pay attention to those people saying that the game's handling and physics are horrible. It's an arcade game and it was designed to be so, so don't expect reallistic collisions, steering, car damage or anything like that. It has very good mechanics for an arcade game. It's not just an ""accelerate and steer game"" and you can still make mistakes in it, considering that you're playing on hardcore mode.I give this game a solid 7.8/10If you have any doubts if you should or should not buy the game, feel free to ask me any questions ; )"
