76561197982554011,Recommended,241560,21137698,"Posted: 11 February, 2016",all,Anodized Wolf,"I can definitely recommend this game if you like racing games. Now that Atari sadly enough announced that they didn't make any more Test Drive games, I saw this come out. It was so good and very similar to the Test Drive games, but kinda with an upgrade so it had so much more potential.Such as:You could earn money quite fast, so there wasn't any hardcore grinding.It has a minimum playtime of roughly 24 hours, before you have seen or discovered the most the game potential.It was easy and fast to get the basic mechanics.The variety of the nature and the roads are of high quality and makes it more interesting to drive around and explore.What I found out playing this game:(I think this can count as a spoiler for some people, just to let you know)In the beginning where everything was new and amazing it was extremely detailed and so much fun. The upgrades on the cars was just so crazy compared to my thoughts that it it couldn't get any better. The singleplayer campaign was dramatic and intense.... - But towards the end of the game I felt that the publisher of the game, (mainly Ubisoft), was in a hurry to get it out to the original date or something, because the gameplay began to be less detailed and the singleplayer campaign just ended in such a weird way and was such a big let-down, compared to what it lead up to.I mean, I was to satisfied and couldn't wait till the end and with the cars' upgrades that was sobadasslooking I thought it was the best game ever basically. Near the end of the game and as well as I began to see the most expensive cars that I had been long waiting for, it seemed like you could only buy the main upgrade for a certain road type and the basic car colour. In the beginning you could upgrade the road type for the car but also the very specific colour even in a anodized way as well. You could upgrade it the smallest parts of the car without any problems.So I mean, it was an extremely good, detailed and satisfying game overall, even for a minor car enthusiastic as myself. But towards the endUbisoftandIvory Towerwas kind of ""slacking"" I guess. It really felt like it was made in a hurry towards the end, so the content took an unsuspected turn.If you are here for the multiplayer part only, you are pretty much good to go. There are nearly no problems whatsoever, but I can only talk for myself here. In multiplayer it was hard to meet up with other players for an extended period of time. As I drove past the edge of a state into another, I kept getting phased out and everybody around me disappeared and new players would come up. I could, however, still see them on the map.So as a summary I will definitely recommend this game for people who like cars and/or details. If you are here for the story or a long game with your friends, I will recommend to buy it cheap or just not to the normal price at least.EDIT: So this game has not been cheap. I bought it with a big discount of 50% for the ""Gold"" edition, which basically means that you get all the DLCs in the same purchase. - Kinda like the game itself and the season pass for most other games. Though after a little while the game devs released a major DLC pack called Wildrun. This DLC wasNOTa part of the season pass and still isn't and it cost 30 euros. I thought that the gold edition would give me that too.. And now that I don't really play the game anymore I randomly saw an announcement for the game on Ubisoft for September 2016 saying you casn get a free copy of the basic game, which I again feel a little sad about.With that being said, it is a beautiful game but overall the price is quite a ripoff."
