,Recommended,241560,22125952,"Posted: 29 March, 2016",all,Despooked,"There are few games I actually like enough to write reviews about (and they mostly suck in quality too) but this game desereves an honest review.Ofcourse a lot of people are♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥about the season pass not including the Wild Run DLC but I never bought a season pass or the wild run, I just bought this game on sale because I wanted to play an good looking open world racing game and this one was worth the 14 euros I spend on it in a sale.So lets start with the storyMany racing games lack a story entirely or just have a basic one.This game is no difference, although the game has a lot more effort in giving a race an purpose, every race has a few lines of voice acting giving the context why you do it. so its not just ""why did I just ram some random car off the road"" in which the game responds ""because OH HEY LOOK REWARDS!""The story itself to spoil the least, Alex Taylor is a racer that wants to join the 5-10's but on the day he would get his ink his brother gets shot by Shiv and then you pretty much try to raise yourself in the 5-10 ranks to get revenge. (again im pretty much just explaining it bare bones there is a lot more to it).For a racing game story i'll give it a: 7/10For a general game story its a: 5/10 characters dont get any in-depth storyGraphicsThe Graphics in this game are really good. shadows look great. cars super detailed. first person driving looks great too. Rain is stunning.Night time is a little bright if you aren't in a shadow or if it' s raining. the world itself is detailed and there are people on the streets just walking around, some carrying stuff. (i even hit some hobo with a shopping trolley once) there is also wildlife running around from squirrels to moose. (Ofcourse it being a ubisoft game there is no senseless killing so you cant actually hit the people or animals) The forests feel dense and real.There is even an in-game photo mode which allows you to take your own pictures in a higher resolution then you actually run the game. I have made a ton of screenshots using it and I even have a few new Computer backgrounds thanks to it.There are a few pre-rendered cutscenes. Which im actually still trying to figure out if they are real recordings with the character models 3d rendered into them or if they are actually modelled so well that they look photo realistic.The bad few things include:A few floating rocks and tree's in forest areas off track.Character faces in game up close are really ugly compared to the rest of the game.short draw distance on cars (detailing like spoilers dissapear if they go a little far away even on ultra). wheel tracks also do not stay long, in the ending cutscene the camera pans into the distance following your car which is outside of the draw distance so it isent visible. Dust trails are really small (so small that if you look behind yourself in first person you dont see any dirt/dust kick up)Mirror's have no real time reflection. (only like GTA V does. reflects low res world but no cars or anything) No option to enable a HUD rear view mirror.AI cars in photo-mode dissapear after a short while due to the fact that the game is online and the cars drive on going beyond draw distance and de-spawning.Graphically for a racing game this is the prettiest game I have played. 9/10 (compared to other racing games like Need for speed)The GameplayFirst the biggest thing I like is the fact that there are more then 2 cars on the road. on highways in major cities you can actually end up just rushing past a continous row of cars. so driving on roads feel actually used instead of the ghost roads you drive on in games like Need For Speed.Cars handle pretty good, feel heavy and in control. I barely drove any other cars then the forced cars and the starting car you pick though. (yes you can easily complete the whole game with the starting car), I've only had 3 occasions of physics doing weird and getting launched at crazy speeds. a few AI cars also glitch sometimes but there is nothing massive as far as i noticed.The special thing about this game is the always online world.So far as i noticed the map is devided in section servers. Major cities have a special server and the country around those cities have seperate servers. I personally have a good internet connection and the server crossings have been seamless. no lag, no freezes, no ""connecting to server"" stuff.Ofcourse if you are like me you coulden't care less about the online stuff and rather don't have any online stuff.there sadly isen't a offline mode. but the game plays pretty much single player, nothing online is forced on you, you could play it as if it were a single player game. Every race can be done solo (meaning you and AI).The AI is easy. As far as I noticed there is no difficulty curve (but this could also be because racing might be one of the game types im decently skilled at) The difficulty is addaptive to your cars level. so if a mission says its hard it's most likely easy if you actually know how to drive well. I even ended up having a 10 second split time on a hard mission.I should also not forget to mention that this game is not your generic ""buy parts in the shop to upgrade"" type. you unlock the parts after every race depending on how well you did. so being first doesent mean a gold part.once you reach level 50 (the max level) you get platinum ratings which use ""smart loot"" as far as i noticed its not that smart and is just an fancy name for ""randomized loot""There are also on road skill challenges a few are:Speed: drive on the road as fast and far as possibleJump: Jump over a ramp into a landing zonePrecision: squeeze through gates that become smaller and smallerSlalom: drive around postsThese also use the bronze, silver, gold loot system.The BadThis game also features Cops. Which are no threat at all and barely worth mentioning except for in the ""escape from the cops"" missions.They barely do anything. you can speed past them at 300 Kmp/h and then wont do a thing.The only few times i've gotten in a chase was when I purposely rammed the cop car or rammed a bunch of AI cars and objects.If you do manage to get into a chase. well they arent that good either. if you want to have a good chase your better off playing Need for Speed Carbon or Most Wanted 2005.You can get 6 stars which only changes how many cars chase you. at 4 you get a helicopter after you (which is the only hard enemy to lose) Road blocks are mostly 1 car and a police sign or on highways like 3 cars and a sign so easily avoided and they will not use Spike Strips or anything like that.You can't disable the road skills meaning you either have to go around or start it and then close it via your phone.I still rate gameplay an 8/10 due to how good the cars feltSoundtrackNot so much to say about the soundtrack. most missions have a special soundtrack which is mostly dramatic orchestral and a bit electric.The in-game radio stations aren't that great either. I mainly listened to 2 of them, Koda boom for in the city and Sine wave digital for the countryside.There is a ""custom"" playlist option which means ""pick songs from our radio stations!"" and no importing of your own music.(a huge thing that bugged me was how the power glove songs (from Far cry 3 blood dragon) still had the in game sound effects in them. You made the game how do you not have a clean version!)In races where there was no special soundtrack I would open my steam overlay and just look up some other music.So the music in this game gets a 4/10 you might like the tracks in the game though. It's just a matter of taste.Story. Graphics. Gameplay. sountrack. that's about everything I think, and im running out of Review space.Well for the TL:DR people:its a good racing game that is worth playing if on sale.rating 8/10"
