76561198084841887,Recommended,241560,13290497,"Posted: 8 December, 2014",all,Bender Rodriguez -F1AK-,"Do I recommend this game?Yes, I had a lot of fun playing itWould I pay full price for it?No, wait until it's on sale. It's good and I enjoyed it, but not that much.Note: It's an arcade style game so I've judged it accordingly. IMO a lot of people are judging the car physics and handling etc like they would for simulators, but it is an arcade game so judge it on it's merits. For an arcade style game I think it does really well.Pros:- Fun single player: Combined the typical ""Need for Speed"" storyline elements with the GTA style open world roaming allowing you to pick and choose your missions- Co-op can be done on any missions, you can do everything on your own or with friends, you don't need to be alone for some missions or with friends for others- Graphics are great- Haven't encountered ANY issues with the game at all- Hidden cars are found by exploration and unlocking areas of the map, not just winning races and earning moneyCons:- Story Mode isn't very long, I've finished it in 18 hours and I didn't use quick travel at all so spent quite a long time driving to some missions- Limited selection of cars, possibly because they decided to make DLC but would've been better if they were available as part of the core game- Not many ""customisation options"" at all: This is for both car customisation and audio/graphics/display settings etc. There's really not that much at all compared to other PC games out there- Limited replayability: There are some bonus missions and ""skills""  and stuff for completionists to do but other than multiplayer with friends and a few longer missions, there's nothing really to do after you finish the game until more missions are released with the upcoming DLC next year, assuming you buy itOverall, I had fun playing it and would recommend you buy it too if you've enjoyed Need for Speed/Burnout style games in the past, then you'll likely enjoy this too. I would however wait until it is cheaper before purchasing it."
