,Recommended,241560,26601751,"Posted: 14 November, 2016",all,Kailen,"This game is silly.  Physics are merely a suggestion.  Cars, even parked ones, will periodically float off into space for no apparent reason.  You vehicles can get sandwiched between an opponent and a wall and sent hurtling off in a random direction or fly through the map.  There is even one skill point where, if you attempted to do it in a certain direction, you WILL be sent off the map.  The AI sometimes breaks, and gets stuck trying to get to a checkpoint, or doesn't realize that it's missed a checkpoint and appears at the finish line doing doughnuts while waiting for you.  The game's story is the most cliche and stereotypical street racing story line that's featured in almost every movie and game on the subject.And it is glorious.There's a lot to do in the game.  Even more with the expansion pack.  (At the time of writing, Wild Run has been released, but not Calling All Units, which I am eagerly awaiting.)  Several races, including an up to almost four hours (in reality can be finished in around three) endurance race.  A few different game modes, including an annoying ""drive over the boxes"" mission type, or a few where you need to try to knock out another car.  Lots of pain jobs and ""stickers"" to apply to cars, as well as some visual customization (though some are quite lacking).  Unlocking everything can take quite some time, and some of the in-game achievements won't trigger properly.  There's PVP, and you can group up with three other friends to do the races and events together.  With the expansion pack you can set up your own races, and accept random stunts.This is not a serious racing game.  It's pretty arcadey with an open world.  But it is fun.  It's great to laugh at the game when it just goes wrong.  The races can be a lot of fun.  Even just driving around can be enjoyable.  Grab the game and a group of friends and just cruise around the USA.  See who can make the best, or worst, cars.  (No under-lights available, sadly.)  Compete with each other on skill points.  Just don't expect a Forza style realistic simulator.  Accept that this game is DUMB and embrace it, and you can have one of the more entertaining driving experiences out there.(Note: I played the game on Uplay for months before getting a complete version on Steam.)"
