,Recommended,241560,13199965,"Posted: 2 December, 2014",all,GaijinGhost,"Everything Test Drive Unlimited should have been, and almost like Horizon on steroids... It's not very often we get a racing game like this on PC, if ever.The Good:-Handling far improved from the Beta, especially if using a controller-Tuning/Customization is one of the most fun aspects of the game, it's not perfect and I'd love to see some more options like airride and ornamental lighting, but a very well implemented system none the less-Huge Open World, drive wherever you want with no boundaries, tones of US landmarks and official Race Tracks, one of my favorite aspects-In-Game Purchases: Now you may ask ""why is this listed under the good?"", let me explain.. I in no way condone in-game purchases or P2W modeled games, but in here it's different. While you can pay real money for cars/customization objects, EVERYTHING in the game can be bought with ingame credits, and even if you make an in-game purchase like I did for a vehicle, you may have a slight edge to beginwith in your story missions, but by the time you hit end game content everyone is really even, so not necessarily ""good"", but it's for those of us who want instant gratification rather than grinding.The Bad:-Car Selection.... As much as I love Muscle cars and the usual cookie cutter Exotics, where are the Japanese imports? Especially for a game with that Fast & Furious feel. Nissan is the only JDM Manufacturer in the Game and only includes the R34 Skyline GT-R and the 370z, I'm a Subaru fan myself and in a game with offroad aspects it was very sad to see them not make the cut.-The Story, while I did enjoy some aspects of the story, this is definitely an MMO style game first and single player game after. It's not terrible, but it does feel like it was thrown in as a simple way to introduce all the mechanics of the game.-Mission Payouts: While you will recieve a decent payout from missions, these missions can sometimes take up to 15 mins of your time, awarding a measly $3k if you're lucky, while some of the PVP missions can award upwards of $20k in as little as 3 minutes.Final Score: 8/10Like I said, if you're a fan of racing games in general, it's very rarely we see a game anywhere near this good on PC, I've got just under 30 hours in and the game released 4 days ago. If you love cars, get it. If you're a little iffy, wait for a sale but definitely worth a play."
