 your ""fellow"" interceptors don't knock you 10 miles in the opposite direction because reasons... same with other player cops...As for single player content...The new character is awful. Seriously. Absolutely horrible.The missions are boring and easy... and there aren't many of them.So...TL;DRThe Crew - It's a good racing game with a whole bunch of content! Not perfect but not bad! 7/10Wild Run - Amazing. Does exactly what you want from an expansion; more content and more hours of fun! 8.5/10!Calling All Units - Utter garbage. I do NOT recomend this expansion. At all.But yeah. The game is great fun! Calling All Units crippled it slighly, but it's still great!"
,Recommended,241560,13267583,"Posted: 7 December, 2014",all,SneakyGingy,"Edit:  It was increasingly harder to find those willing to dedicate time to Co-Op missions with me around levels 40-50.  Also, I also get ""no one is in your session"" a bit.  Not very ""MMO"" but I still enjoyed the playthrough, will continue playing, and I'm interested to see if something happnes to make finding races with others a bit easier.Edit:  Ok, now it seems a bit broken.  I was wrapped up in the story line and getting ot level 50.  I can see how getting involved with the faction and rising up the tiers there would be interesting... but there is never anyone to co-op with.   Not much of a ""MMO""....So, there have been some mixed reviews about The Crew.  Most of them comparing this game to other games like Forza Horizon 2 (Amazing game) and the NFS series.  Remember, this is its own game.  Take it for what it is:  an arcade style racing game with the capability to connect with others in an open world setting.  In that sense, the game completely delivers.I haven't encountered any bugs or issues except for one disconnect a few days ago.   I also think a few of these reviews haven't given the game enough effort.  They're complaining about not getting gold/platinum parts or that people can pay for them.  Absolutely they can pay for them, but they can also be earned.  That's part of the challenge and the parts are wtihin reach.The car list isn't extensive which is a bit upsetting and Ubisoft should really release them instead of making us pay.  That would really be my only complaint.  Tons of customization is available and the story line really isn't that bad.  I actually enjoy the cutscenese inbetween moving from city to city to try and build the 5-10 reputation and get to Coburn.It is also worth noting that as you progress, new race modes are made available and features to immerse you further into The Crew such as factions and different classes.I honestly believe some of the backlash is 