76561198234175720,Recommended,241560,17420964,"Posted: 6 August, 2015",all,McLaren19,"The Crew is a good game despite the reviews and other stuff other people have said about it. It does have it's flaws, but they are far out-weighed by the Pros.Pros:-Vast Open World to explore (Bigger than Test Drive Unlimited/Test Drive Unlimited 2's map)-Large amount of cars to buy and customize-The amount of customization is rather large-Each Spec you acquire for a car creates a new car with it's own customization. So 5 Specs would equal 5 different cars-Performance Parts for cars can be entirely earned without money by completing Skills in the Open WorldCons:-Micro Transactions-Payouts from missions and activities is low-Car physics get buggy when driving over certain features (ie Rocks/Cliffs) [This can also be fun and make funny moments. so maybe not so much a bad thing]-Campaign/Career is rather short.-You must be connected to the internet at all times when you playThese are just a few of the pros and cons. Again the pros outweigh the cons, and cruising with your friends makes it even better. I would recommend getting the game on sale or at least getting the Season Pass to save money on the DLC. This game is overall a great game. I would give it a 8.5 out of 10. It has a lot of replay value, making it worth purchasing.Hope this review helps."
