,Recommended,241560,19728358,"Posted: 16 December, 2015",all,Mr. Ethical,"Back when the trailer was announced for The Crew, I was actually highly anticipated. The huge map, the car spec system, and being set in an alive world with players playing around (basically MMO racing) is like a dream come true for me. I never got into playing the beta, so I have to wait until the game is released. But at that point, I haven't bought the game yet. When the reviews first rolled out, it turns out it wasn't that great, so I decided to hold out until the price drop.Apparently they released a demo, and I downloaded the demo and played it for 2 hours (the whole duration of the demo) to get the feel of the game. Needless to say, the resolution was tobuy it + Wild Run.I find the driving to be extremely relaxing. Driving to an undiscovered area isn't a complete chore - in fact, in some places, even fun. The spec system is genius, allowing you to have that same car without buying another one (because the prices for it are ludicrous). And, of course, you have the WHOLE US to drive in WITH ALMOST NO RESTRICTION. The collectables are also fun to collect. The game also provides a lot of content (besides the map).Providing a demo is also commendable - not a lot of AAA pubs provide a demo nowadays.But, of course, the game isn't perfect. In fact, it's more flawed than I thought it would be. The physics are probably the main weakness of the game. Cars drive fine at the intended purpose, but when you don't use it as intended, it starts to bounce around literally everywhere. The collision physics is also bad, because as you bump a car, instead of colliding as usual, the car sometimes slides off it and you lose control. Not to mention, you can just drift into a wide corner, ignoring the fact that you'll smash a few fences and go through nasty bumps without losing a single speed. Story is pretty clichéd  and predictable. Game can be a bit grindy. AI racers are inconsistent (most of my encounters are easy though).Not to mention, it's Ubisoft, so expect MICROTRANSACTIONS.About Wild Run, I think I made a bad decision for buying it. It's not a bad add-on, but it's not worth buying. It allows you to buy a few bikes, an access to the monthly Summit event, and Extreme specs. The Extreme specs are, needless to say, lazily done as they only use customizations from Perf and Dirt specs. Drag spec physics is also too random, which pisses me off as it won't allow me to get the best time at Drag events. Monster physics are also messed up, and is easily exploitable. Drift is actually pretty fine. Bikes are pretty weird to control - it's not as agile as described.I am, myself, a racing fan since I got my first PS1 back when I was 7 years old, so if you're like me you'll probably find The Crew to be favorable. However, if you only moderately like racing games and would expect a game like the earlier NFS or something like Project CARS, you won't get it here. After the price drop, it is worth it, but I recommend you try out the demo provided by the developers."
