,Recommended,241560,13728014,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,Krakdotz,"TL:DR: I recommend this game if you enjoy Arcade style racing. I may not like many things about the game, but the big issues, like no rear view mirrors in cockpit view, can easily patched out. I hope to see enough support for this game to see expansions like Canada, Mexico, and Europe as additional places you can go (maybe with a 10 level increase for each one released like WoW.)Overall: 66/130Please remember while reading this is only my opinion and I actually do recommend purchasing the game and playing.Please don't let the low score throw you off. The driving and customization scores can easily go way up by patching Mirrors, damage, more cars and ways to customize them.I'll start off with what it seems they wanted in this game.______________________Miscillaneous: 35/40Originality: 9/10The spec system was interesting, Raid specs were something not really done in a racing game, and involving a purpose for them that was well designed as well.MMO: 9/10It's really actually good. I think it could have been pushed to that 10/10 if it forced you to group with other players for Faction missions instead of being able to solo them. I think they were afraid of not enough people queueing for 2 1/2 hour races though.Story: 8/10I read a review early into playing the game that trashed the story, calling it a ""typical racing game story"". After playing through it I see where this talk would be coming from, but it's really hard not to think they just skipped all of the cinematics because it was actually decent. Towards the end it got a bit old, everybody had these bad blood ties to the last boss with rediculous stories to go along, but the initial event, although obvious, was very well done. The end was also pretty thrilling as you confronted the final boss demanding a race for the V8.Zone emersion: 9/10Each zone really felt like it's own thing. Detroit and Chicago felt like street racing. All the dirt areas really felt like you were driving in a Rally car. When you unlocked perf spec you really feel like you did a bunch of street mods to your car. The mountain states were pretty incredible, and Raid spec for the missions there, you really felt like it was something you were doing. Circuit specs do feel like circuit speed compared to the others and there are lots of actual tracks in the game to go try it out on.So that stuff was fine and dandy. The thing is, none of it is what the majority of people actually play racing games for. A lot of people are either Arcade drivers or Simulation drivers. This game has a middle ground, but anything other than Simulation is still Arcade, and for that most Simulation drivers probably won't like it.__________________Driving: 17/50Handling: 3/10This is because it is too easy to turn, this game has an Arcade feel where late breaking is very forgiven, and proper breaking is punished with early turning.Speed: 4/10It all feels very fast, but not real fast. Either the cars are tiny or the roads and buildings are crazy large, the scaling of going 65-75 mph is not even close to as fast as it is in real life, and inherently the higher speeds arn't either. I beleive it was scaled down to make the map seem larger, things take longer.Mechanics: 2/10Unlimited NOS (aside from the cooldown of refilling) brings this way down. Manual works well in Free Roam. The clutch doesn't seem to do anything when you have an xbox controller, can't say for a steering wheel as I don't have one. There is absolutely no gear grinding when shifting without using the clutch.Camera View: 6/10All the standard views, but the important one when it comes to this category is the Cockpit because it has the most detail. No working mirrors.Damage: 2/10Your car has a healthbar and you need to repair it, but the car will look fresh from the dealer even if it is damaged if you just drive it a bit. Damage does not effect any driving mechanics.So the driving wasn't quite there. I don't play racing games to drive anyway. I personally love customizing, and driving slow in cool cars. I assumed a massive map where other players around the world could see my cars while a went for a slow cruise on the highway would be amazing._______________________Customization: 7/30Performance:  7/10You get to change out a lot of the stuff under the hood. It's just a little far from realistic (being that its just Bronze - Plat LVLX peice)Visual: 0/10Far from the standard. When painting the car you can choose 2 tone but can't choose what part. You can't position vinals and can't have more than one. You can't customize actual peices very well, I have yet to find a car that actually lets you swap out the fenders, and most of the cars only have a couple of choices for each peice, if any.Cars: 0/10There are like none. There is not one Mazda or Subaru in the whole game. I hope there are many more cars added as in game purchaseables. NOT DLC UBISOFT._______________Races: 7/10PVP matchmaking and 3 hour runs for hardcores. Awesome. Starting a lot of the Story races already moving, annoying. When driving manual some of these races you have to be spamming the upshift as it starts because you start the race in 2nd at the red line."
