,Recommended,241560,13872230,"Posted: 6 January, 2015",all,Mega,"Definitely one of the best racing games out there, while the physics are indeed arcade-ish and sometimes your car can spin to hell (fixed on tomorrow, January 7th's update), it should not stop you from having a great experience. However, if you want to have more fun in this game, you should try to get some teammates on first hand to make the overall campaign less frustrating and enjoyable.The storyline features Alex Taylor, an illegal street racer voiced by someone who seems to have a protagonsit fetish, yours truly, Troy Baker. The story is about Alex being framed by a murder he did not commit and his quest for justice and revenge. For a racing game, it's really engaging.The map is really diverse, and it's not filled with random content, you can explore for hours and you'll feel an amazing immersion, no racing game achieved this on me before. Contains all main USA cities, however if you're american, expect a few small towns you know to be missing (Orlando, for starters, is nowhere to be found), but it's the sacrifice you need to make with a game of this scale.The graphics are also really pretty, and Nvidia's graphic features, completely opposite to other older games, does NOT ruin your framerate and performance and it amazingly improves the games' look compared to the console counterparts.AspectScore (out of 10)Gameplay10Story9.5Performance9Graphics10"
