76561198145333765,Recommended,241560,13710080,"Posted: 30 December, 2014",all,Gerbera.Z,"Ok frist things first, I am an Actual Mechanic and Car addict, and I play all genres of games too, so im not too biased I hope.This game is easily misunderstood for a game that should be like Need for Speed and Burnout. No, just stop and think about it, have you noticed how small burnout paradise's and NFS Rival's Map was? Very small indeed, they were both great, but the maps did not deliver. The crew has a gorgeous map, especially for that size, its very detailed and there is so much going on in the background that it gives you that, ""I'm in a living and breathing world feel"". You will seep lanes flying in and out of airports, peopel walking around, ambulances and firetrucks roaring by, heck, sometimes i smack into em' from time to time because they go by so quick. There are alot of players online too, i keep bumping into otther guys and chase em around. for giggles, I smash into em to bother them. There is just too much to do, so many different environments, so many missions, the story makes sense and is pretty interesting for a game this type, but dont expect a deep story like those mass effect games or a visual novel ok? This game aint only about the story, but the point of it is to  DRIVE. this game IS a racing game too, there is alot to race against, wetehr it's time, friends, or the clock. now There are a few issues that I noticed. There is a lack of cars. Lucky for me I love dodges, so there is dodge galore for me and my favorite machine ever is the dodge viper. I guess im just lucky. yeah, the game needs more cars. As for the visuals, ARE YOU REALLY GOING TO EXPECT A GAME THIS SIZE TO LOOK AS GOOD AS DRIVECLUB, FORZA 5, AND PROJECT CARS!? Those games are only on small  maps catered to a certain course, that's why they look so nice, give me a game this big with Driveclub's visuals and i'll drop dead. The engine sounds are quite accurate, I surprised to hear the Dodge RAM SRT 10 sound like the viper, I was shocked they did it right. The cops on the game are a real challenge too. some might get annoyed due to teh dificulty, but I like it alot simply because I found the cops in NFS rivals to be too easy and the same applies to mostly all other games that feature pursuits. There are distinct cops for each city as well as helicopters too. This games is insane. Here now is my final area, the performance on this game. I'm running an overclocked AMD FX processor at 4.41 GHz, an  AMD R9 280X GPU, and 16 GB of RAM. This is by no means the best computer ever, but man it's pretty dammn good at running all games. The crew suffers from stuttering when running 60 fps during cutscenes, and there will be some fps drop a times. I run this game all ultra, and AA at 4x. So it looks easily better than PS4/XB1. The handling is awesome, because it requires skill, i drive with hardcore settings and it allows me to powerslide and control the drifts and such, the standard setting is too easy for me and it makes it so cartoony compared to hardcore. My verdict is that you should try this game because it will be worth it, try get a friend or two in there, or simply make new ones, tehre are many people trying to add me all the time so there will be no shorage of that my friends. Well I hope i didnt waste too much time. Thanks for reading."
