,Recommended,241560,13457710,"Posted: 19 December, 2014",all,HELLAFLUSH,"21 hours in, The Crew gets a lot of bad hype from the playerbase.I'm not too sure why. The GRID-2 esque driving is a letdown, of course. But the open map, beautiful car models, and superb level of customization is something that has me getting back on every single day.Pros -Massive open worldDetail on the cars, though lack of working rearview mirrors annoys me.Halfway decent story (It's nothing special, but it's a nice change from your average G.I. Joe who kills everything with two legs and hair where there shouldn't be).The... Car... Putting itself together... Thing....Very good performance on my systemNative controller support (it's needed and will probably feel better than a wheel, but that's just a thought).Tires work like they do in real life. (That's right,  you'd better learn how to nudge around corners instead of drifting every single one).Cars actually feel different in every single way, from handling, to acceleration, to braking, whether it's 15mph in a Raptor or 145 in a raid spec Mustang.MMO Aspect - The game's MMO aspect is a dual blessing and curse, as situations like this arise.Driving down the road in a performance mod Ford Focus RS.Look up, a player is sitting on the shoulder of the road up ahead.I pull up next to a LaferrariEh, why not? I rev my engineHe revs his. 3 seconds later we shoot off.45 seconds later we reach my turn and I take it, pulling over.5 seconds later the Laferrari chugs up the road.He pauses his game and dissapears.Things like that can happen. Randomly. It's great, you feel like you're more than a tourist in a fast car with an ugly neck tat.Long races.LONG RACES.I've done races that lasted a full 2 1/2 hours.2 hours. 30 minutes. 90 minutes. 60 seconds x 90.I don't care what you're playing. What you're interested in. Where you're from.Or what year the game was made in.If you get to the end of a 2.5 hour race it is epic. No matter what.Non-restrictive racing GPS.In GTAV I had a problem - I memorized the city and it's routes. I knew shortcuts.They didn't help for♥♥♥♥♥♥in races with checkpoints every 30 seconds.In the crew, as long as you hit the next checkpoint (They're often 1-2 minutes away from eachother), you get credit.Want to cut that corner? No fear, the game won't punish you.Going down a hill road with a lot of turns, but there's a jump that can get you to the bottom in 3 seconds flat? As long as there's not a checkpoint on the hill road, the game won't punish you.Want to jump that hill to skip that hard turn? No problem, just watch out for the tree.Cons -May not run well on lower-end systems. (My computer is worth about 1300 dollars, and can run everything but anti-aliasing at it's max setttings, and even then, my GPU is mid-tier).MMO aspect - The MMO aspect to this game is a dual blessing and curse, as situations such as these arise.Players that park their car on challenge courses, speed and Slalom mainly - You have no choice but to miss your objective or hit the car head on at a generally breakneck speed.Players that invite you to co-op missions and leave when you start winning, not knowing if you win they still win - You just wasted your time and have nothing to show for it. Because some kid is butmad.GTA drivers - Kids that ram you every 30 seconds, trying to knock you out of your place because the idea of actually racing to race instead of (theoretically) wasting your thousands of dollar aftermods and paint job on some ninnie who's car is faster. But then again, kids these days haven't been praised for critical thinking.Useless E-brake - Oh yeah, rage all you want. I've yet to come to any hairpin where pumping or locking my main brakes briefly and using nitrous to straighten out didn't work. And I don't jump down to 20mph like I would popping an E brake turn.Car fanboys - I don't care that the GTR isn't right-side drive. It's a game. You want ""your"" GTR to be perfect, you go buy it.PvP - As an MMO player, I have to say one thing - Screw this PvP. There's no ladder or groupings of people of a simillar level. Once you hit level 10, expect to pvp against people with level 1000+ cars. I tried it once, left and only do co-op missions now. Until they can orgainize the PvP better, my suggestion is to stay away until you yourself have a ""min-maxed"" car.Limited (For the moment it seems) car selection -At the time of this review, an update has been added that added about 5 cars to the game free of charge. I hope we can expect more things like this, as it was a welcome change of pace from paying 10 dollars for 2 models of some Audi I'll never drive but only want because muh car collectionArcade-y driving - Yeah, it's like the Call of Duty of racing games. You'll live.TL;DRBuy it if you think you can run it. If you don't, don't waste your money. You'll need more than a half decent PC build (Entire PC build, not just a GPU. If you're running a pentium it doesn't matter what GPU you have, things are going to mess up).Don't upgrade your PC to high end status just for this game. It's not THAT great.Keep Steam online for updates to the game (they don't come from Uplay), otherwise you'll be harassed with error codes."
