,Recommended,241560,13239997,"Posted: 5 December, 2014",all,Ronys2,"Probably one of the better Ubisoft releases yet as far as bugs and server connections go. But as per all Ubisoft games now you need an Uplay account (3rd party DRM). This isn't by any means a simulator racing type of game, it's more of an arcade racing game. Huge open world and plenty of Stuff to do. There's the main story missions, faction races, PVP, and skill missions that build up your cars level and unlock parts for the vehicle you complete the mission with. Co-op works well although its easy to buddy fook your team mates if you run in to them during the races. All the skill missions have global leader boards which allow you to attempt to take over the world record, which adds replay ability. I must have replayed an escape mission in the sand dunes 20-30 time trying to find the best route through the dunes to achieve a top 10 position. The driving in the game feels good, but takes a little bit to get use to the e-brake and drift capabilities on each vehicle. The cars most definitely feel and perform better at higher levels, with a ton of customizability. Vehicles heal themselves visually over a short period of time, but there is an overall health of the vehicle that gets reduced when you have severe wreaks which after so many you will need to head back to a HQ garage to repair up, or use the mobile mechanic to repair at an elevated price. Getting the cops mad can be fun, and a wanted level of 5 stars makes for an interesting escape. Police can mess you up if you make mistakes while attempting to escape (but all you do is pay a fine). Overall the game is very enjoyable and a great play. There's a vehicle for every type of car enthusiast.I give it 7.5/10 Pre DLC."
