,Recommended,241560,13210561,"Posted: 3 December, 2014",all,JDS_mirai,"Ok heres my Review on The Crew.I'll start with networking in this game, as it is a huge issue! For something billed as an MMO... half the time I can't even group up with friends because of some issue with the network. The actual MMO is really a Peer to Peer crap so you only see a handful of players in your session, if even that... half the time as well there my sessions were empty. It's labelled an MMO but I think they decieved alot of people here...Graphics are a hit and miss, sometimes beautiful and gorgeous but most of the time its ugly and bland in other places. Textures were pretty muddy and looked rushed alot. But I love the little details like when you see helicopters flying overhead, and planes/jets whizzing by, it makes you feel immersed in the world, even if it did look like♥♥♥♥♥♥half the time.Gameplay is good.... the map is massive and probably the largest I've seen to date, and easiest the major selling point of the game. You feel like you really are in the USA. Lots of variety of biomes, from snow to desert, forest, urban... beaches... industrial... and just a mindboggling amount of things to see, it really felt like I never saw the same prop or location twice if you know what I mean...  The driving and handling, was servicable as its an arcade racer, so nothing  really here that makes it stand out. It did remind me of NFS Underground though.Story-wise is run of the mill Fast and the Furious movie plot, but it was entertaining for the most part... and at times I really did feel like Brian O'Connor (RIP). But I did started yawning myself to sleep towards the end though....Audio is probably the best element of the game. Best Turbo spool sound EVER in a game. The V8's also sound lumpy and powerful like I expected. Tyres screeching, dirt  flinging around... ambient sounds are great too. I left the music off so I can't comment on the tracks. Voice actors were generally good also, and I did like some of the banter between the actors and some jokes they made especially that of the main.Lastly, and probably my biggest gripe. If you are a fan of Japanese cars or imports you are so out of luck here.The Crew comes only with the Nissan R34 Skyline GTR and the 370Z, which will probably be a huge deal breaker and F*CK U  to 90% of the car enthusiast community. Everything else is probably a mix between American muscle and European Exotics. It's solely because of this that I will probably not recommended this game. What good is a driving game that the cars you drive you don't enjoy driving? Wheres the AE86 or Supra? Where's the RX7 and RX8? Where's the Silvia's? The WRX/EVO? The Civic/Integra/NSX?In the end, I will probably give it a 6/10.... taking 2 points off for the mentioned lack of JDM cars. This is a big issue to me, but may not be for some others.Also if you are against microtransactions and DLCs, take off another point or two. Its all here, as expected from an Ubisoft published game. Money is obviously designed to be hard to make in this game, to pave the way for the buying of credits with real money... yeah its pay to play guys. You can finish they game and hardly have enough to even buy that 1 million dollar hummer... without grinding some more for eternity before you just give up and open your wallet....If you can look past those issues then its a solid game worthy of a look, especially since there aren't many open world racers on the PC these days.Edit: Ok I bumped up another point to a total 6/10.. due to I think I am a little unfair in my review.... and it is a fun game! Just not what I expected as an 'MMO', network problems, and due to the  lack of cars aspect of my review... but after playing a little more I think it does genuinely deserves a thumbs up... but only just..."
