,Recommended,241560,13525305,"Posted: 22 December, 2014",all,clachcik7,"The Crew is an amazing achievement of a game. Especially by Ubisoft, which I keep forgetting they made the game. It's an open world (literally, the entire United States at your disposal) racing game with an arcade-like control scheme and a wide selection of vehicles. There are thousands of missions, side quests, mini games, and PVP lobbies to enjoy and they really do pull you into this vast open world game. I have driven across the United States many times in real life and they really capture alot of the beauty our country has. It's not ""exactly"" a representation of this country but its got its landmarks and alot of things I reconigize (like the oil fields and empty backroads in Amarillo texas and the swamps through the south in Louisana and alot of the beautiful wooded areas and mountains of Maine). This game is very addicting and I have over 17 hours of gameplay. It's hard sometimes and its mostly those hairpin turns and the traffic that♥♥♥♥♥♥me off the most. I keep on having to retry alot of the challenges because I'm shooting for that gold medal. The way it grades you during the main missions I don't like very much because in the end, if you win and you're in 1st place, you should automatically get a gold medal. I don't know how it grades you but I keep getting bronze and silver medals even if I win 1st place in the main missions. There are also hour long missions that take forever, so I reccommend that if you're not playing with friends, play those missions in solo so you can pause the game and take a break after holding down the R-trigger for a half hour or more. When it says ""1 Hour"" in length, it really means it too. I still have a long ways to go, I'm level 35 and I own a handful of cars (I bought out all the Mustangs since they are my favorite cars and I think I got an F150 too) but I wish there was a way to sell or trade vehicles between players because each car is unique when you start unlocking parts for them and there is a wide selection of parts and add-ons so there will never be an exactly identical vehicle for as long as this game survives. I wish more people would buy this game or at least get it when it's on sale. It is worth the $60 and the fact that its an online open world racing game without a monthly fee just makes it all the better. I hope they come out with alot of DLC for this and maybe expand the map across North and South America and maybe even make a sequel that will take us across the world to other countries too. I highly reccommend this game to anybody who loves racing games (I usually suck at them but after playing this game this long I've gotten used to the genre alot more and I've even improved my skills in games like GRID 2 and NFS Rivals)."
