,Not Recommended,241560,35421622,Posted: 2 October,all,Tomm,k
,Recommended,241560,11864223,"Posted: 25 August, 2014",all,Twiggy,"This is based on the Beta as of August 25th:I realize this is a beta and there may or may not be changes made to the things that I list, and if they have been changed after this review I will change it. That being said I'll begin my review.First impressions of this beta leave a lot to be desired. There are a couple things that I feel that ruin the immersion of the game and give it an unrealistic feel. The biggest example of this would be the car physics and handling. I understand that they are going for a more arcadey feel to the handling, and I went into the beta with full understanding of this. However, I feel that the handling could be improved. As it stands right now, the cars feel very ""floaty"". It feels as if the cars just slide around on the road, making them more difficult to drive than expected. This could be due to the strange sense of speed, which I will explain later on. There also seems to be a slight control input delay which could be a factor into this floaty feeling. It's not much of a delay, but just enough to feel it. I don't know if it's intentional to simulate the car having some weight but I feel as of right now that it is a little too much. Bear in mind I am playing with an Xbox 360 controller, and have not tried The Crew with a wheel or keyboard.The second thing that I noticed is the sense of speed. You do not feel like you are going as fast as you really are, which can lead to you misjudging corners and braking. As mentioned before, this probably attributes to the floaty feeling of the cars, since at higher speeds I would expect the cars to drift around. Some minor tweaks like adding more motion blur to the edge of the screen would help, even narrowing the field of view as you increased speed to simulate tunnel vision.So far that is my biggest concern with the game apart from obvious glitches and crashes which is to be expected in a beta. I am enjoying it quite a bit in the free ride and I feel once my friends get into the beta it'll be even more fun to drive around. It seems like it has a lot of potential to be a great casual racing game, but for me the actual racing isn't as fun due to, in my opinion, the strange handling of the cars. Offroad is a tun of fun especially in Raid Spec vehicles. and doing cross country trips is a blast.As far as graphics go, it's a great looking game, but it's not the best, which is fine by me. The damage modeling seems a bit over exaggerated, you hit a fence pole and suddenly you have a dent in the front bumper that would crush your engine block. The game is fairly well detailed especially in the customization. You can strip your car down and see the internals of your engine and gearbox, which while it isn't necessary, it is nice to see them putting in extra detail.There is a ton of customization options as far as body kits and rims. I love the fact that they added offical rims to the cars, instead of generic rims (which can still be used if you'd like). There are tons of bumpers, side skirts, hoods, and spoilers to choose from, although some of the bumpers do seem so much alike I couldn't tell a difference.Overall if I had to I suppose I would recommend the game, but not by much. The potential is there, but it does seem to be lacking in some areas and even though it's a beta there's no guarantee that these things will improve. If you haven't preordered it yet, just wait and see how the reviews are after release. To me it's not preorder worthy, and I may ask for a refund by the end of this beta and wait and see."
