,Recommended,241560,24122302,"Posted: 5 July, 2016",all,neoman,"It's hard to fully describe the charms in The Crew. It's a driving game more than a racing game, it's a broken MMO, it's a semi functional Diabloesque Car-RPG, It's a run of the mill single player game.And then again, it's a work of art, with one of the most fully realised open worlds ever built, featuring the entire USA, with it's most recognizable cities, mountains, forests, with every square inch drivable, with dynamic weather and day-night cycles, where you can feel the pleasure of driving with a small but ecletic selection of vehicles, in beautifully rendered cockpits, every vehicle completely customizable, and travel anywhere you want in this huge map right from the start.With the possibility for friends to join you in these roadtrips, and in the campaign mode, the pleasure is amped the amount of friends you manage to play with.Word of the advice: the default steering settings are too floaty and unintuitive for some people, me included, but with every driving setting available for you to tweak at your leisure, the game will certainly fit every racing enthusiast's preferences wit a bit of fiddling and pacience.-to sum up: this is one of the most ambitious games out there, beautiful graphics, and a huge and atmospheric world where you can give wings to your driving fantasies, certainly one of the most underrated titles of recent years, and indeed deserving of a chance and a closer look from everyone who enjoys the simple pleasure of driving."
