76561198047686869,Recommended,241560,16654737,"Posted: 23 June, 2015",all,Hannibal802,"The game is pretty good for what it is, it's a car game. The racing is alright, it's not challenging. Leveling up your car doesn't seem to make the races any easier or harder because the AI adjusts to your speed. There is a lot of exploration. I finished the story in 11 hours of gameplay, fairly short story, but there are loads of challenges to still do, cars to collect and customize. The races you do get repetitive, there are races against the clock, races against AI point to point and circuit, takedown, escape the cops. You start in a fantasy America with real major cities. Detroit is where you start with tuner class cars. From there you go to New York and dirt class cars. Miami is next with performance cars. Las Vegas next with raid cars, and finally Los Angeles and circuit cars. I'd give it an 8/10, it's pretty good what what it is, could be improved for sure. It's great fun with a friend or two."
