,Recommended,241560,14942751,"Posted: 17 March, 2015",all,Gizmo,"While I do recommend this game please understand that most of the bad reviews are true and should be taken into consideration when purchasing.  I bought this game knowing what I was getting into and wow was some of it terrible.Setup:It took me 40 minutes to even get the game to let me map my wired Xbox 360 controller.  It required me to restart after every key otherwise it wouldn't save the key mapping.  That isn't the worst part about the controls though.Controls:The worst part is the fact that the game doesn't take an analog reading for the joystick.  What this means is any direction you turn no matter how little it jumps 100% in that direction making this game a fishtailing mess.  In game menus require you to use the keyboard because the make the 4 different menus in the game require different buttons and a controller only has one D-pad.Cops:The cops are pretty dumb, if you drive in a straight line the cops will magically be able to drive as fast as you and you will never lose them.  As soon as you make a few quick turns they are lost.  The chopper is the same way as the cop cars.  I wish they used spike strips and strategic placements in the cities rather than the boring same way every time to get rid of the cops.Civilians:There is a decent amount of traffic (sometimes on a rare occasion I can't find a car for miles) and it is randomly generated.  The only problem is it is randomly generated in groups.  So rather than a car here and there it will be 20 cars taking up all the lanes then a 1/4 mile of no cars.  This gets annoying with the controls as mentioned earlier.Audio:I am using a high end sound card with a nice Sennheiser headphones in this game and all I have to say is the cars do sound different from one another but they sound boring; with the exception of a few cars.  All the cars sound like they run really poor when at idle.  They make horrible ping noises and run rough it is kind of funny.  The tires make the same screeching noise whether they are on asphalt or dirt.  I will say the pedestrians have very good placement and freak me out every time because I think someone is sitting next to me.Graphics:This game looks like it’s from and Xbox 360.  Seriously it looks pretty poor and the attention to detail on things like no functioning review mirror or side mirrors is just sad.  I play in 4k on ultra-settings on two 660 FTW and an i5 @ 4.4 GHz and I will say both GPU's are pinned at 100% and CPU is around 70%.  So it's not very efficient, BF4 runs better on the same ultra-settings.  With that said I don't ever have any dips below 30 FPS it is always running smooth so I guess that is good.  Just realize this game is only around 14 GB which is incredibly small for a game with such a large map.  This goes to show you how low res the textures in the game are.Map:Everyone talks about how awesome the map is; this is the reason I bought the game.  Let me say the map is larger than any game I've played.  With that said there are only a few cities and the rest is just a highway attaching states so it is much smaller than I anticipated.  With that said I have much to see with 30+ hours of playing at the time of writing this.  I put this game on an SSD and it was the best game you could ever put on an SSD.  After seeing complaints about how slow all the constant loading screens are and moving in the map I have not had this problem.  Everything happens within a second or so.Racing:Look the story line may be terrible but it is definitely bearable and I enjoy it being there.  There just isn't much motivation to complete it other than to unlock tuning shops that are only useful once.  Leveling up is done much faster on PVP races even if you come in last every race.  The parts you win are no different than any other short challenge scattered across the map.  Speaking of skill challenges, there are about 5 different challenges and you just do the same thing over and over but in a different area.  It's the exact same problem with the main story as well.  Yet I still find myself going back and completing them in between story missions.    The biggest problem I have with this game is when you hit level 50.  That is the top level you can reach and it unlocks the ability to get special parts in any skill challenge.  The problem is I can go back to a skill level 1 challenge and win the same part on a skill level 50 challenges that is way harder.Conclusion:Look this review has been super negative about the game yet I still recommend it.  The reason is because I am playing it about 8 hours a day since I got it.  Even with all of these issues I still enjoy seeing all of the ugly scenery and driving around in all of the terrible driving cars.  So if you can live with all of the issues mentioned above I recommend the game on a sale like the way I got it.  I do not recommend it at $60.  I wish they would have split the US into 3 sections and charged $60 per-section.  It sounds crazy but with a higher budget and a year in between each section the game could have been so much more.  The map would be the same size but California wouldn't have been cut off at Sacramento and the “Mountain States” wouldn’t be empty along with all of the problems plaguing the game would be fixed."
