,Recommended,241560,15085103,"Posted: 27 March, 2015",all,Hyp5r,"Sure, this game gets a lot of hate because it's not truly an MMO, the car selection is pretty weak, the handling of the cars leave much to be desired, the rubberbanding, it goes on and on and on, but the truth is, this game is pretty damn fun.If you're playing for the story, expect a poor performance.  No racing game has ever had a story (to my knowledge) that will keep you on your toes and leave you satisfied.  However, playing this game with random people or your friends, you can have a hell of a time from crusing, racing on-road & off-road, performing skill challenges, and more.Truth be told. it's probably one of the better racing games out on PC right now, for those who like arcade-style racing and an active community.  Unfortunately, the other game that fits this itch better would be Test Drive Unlimited 2, which doesn't have much of a community anymore (though many still play it).Another downside is an always-on connection to Ubisoft.  Even though you can complete everything in single-player, you must be online and connected to the Uplay servers, otherwise you'll be booted out to the main menu.  This can become a real annoyance if you just happen to be in an event and lose your internet connection.There's definitely a lot wrong with this game, but there's a lot right too.  The map is absolutely gigantic, and driving from A to B is pretty damn nice visually.  The time of day, weather (as in clouds and snow, no rain for some reason), they both lead to some very pretty visuals.  While some criticize the physics, I actually like them, save for the fact that flipping is an instant crash.  The cars are all very fun to drive, and can be customized to your own wants and needs, visually and performance-wise.  Of course, the way this game handles performance is odd, since a Mini Cooper can be as fast as a LaFerrari, but other than that ...Overall, this game scratches an itch for me.  I've always loved community-style racing, and this game does fit that budget.  While Test Drive Unlimited 2 is definitely an alternative to this game, The Crew does have a little more in terms of graphics and physics, but a lot less in terms of selection.  Truth be told, if you've played TDU2, there's little to expect from this game.  For those looking for an entry into racing, this game isn't half-bad to start out with."
