76561198087730801,Recommended,241560,13517499,"Posted: 21 December, 2014",all,durablecardboard,"Overall, a decent game. Story isn't half bad, the map is HUGE (some races literally take well over an hour to complete, and you don't even see 25% of the map in those races), and there are a few really cool cars. The level of detail in this game is incredible. I'm not a fan of the butchered geography of the United States, but they (for the most part) captured the feel of all the different areas of the country. It really does feel like I am driving across the prarie of my home in Wyoming, the east coast really looks like the east coast, and New Mexico looks like New Mexico. I am impressed. I'm a racing game junkie and I love this game. The multiplayer is phenominal and I love the incorporation of MMO style to the game. I would have to say this is probably the best racing game since the first Need for Speed: Most Wanted came out on the original XBOX. The challenges that are spread out throughout the game definately keep things interesting and alleviate some of the hum-drum-ness that accompanies the long drives in this game.However...There are a few bad things to this game. Some of this is nit-picking, but I feel like the main points are valid complaints.1. The AI cars are nearly impossible to beat. They accelerate harder, go faster, and recover from crashes way faster than you ever could. If you want to take first in almost any long distance event, you had better make sure your car is well over 100 levels higher than the game recommends or you won't have a chance in H-E-double hockey sticks to ever hold first long enough to come in first. Same thing applies to the police and hitmen trying to run you off the road. They are stupidly fast and hard to dodge.2. The scoring system. The game makes it nearly impossible to take a gold medal in an event. You need to hold first place for over 90% of the race, not hit like anything and come in first to take the gold. This is an extremely hard scale to beat, especially when you factor in the god-like AI cars (that can be well over 100 levels below you and still accelerate harder and have a top speed of literally one or two mph faster than your car) and the questonable physics engine (more on that next paragraph) The missions where you ditch the AI cars are also difficult to take gold in becuase you simultaneously have to do incredible amounts of damage to the cops and evade them quickly. If the mission goes over like two minutes you won't get gold, no matter how much damage you did to the cops. And its really hard to get away from them and damage them because hitting them seems to make them mad and harder to get away from. It just really seems like the scoring system is heavily stacked against you.3. The physics for this game. Especially when it comes to off-road vehicles. I don't know of anyone who would want to drive well over 130 mph off road. Going this fast lends itself to some incredibly difficult handling off road. The game was very well designed, map wise, but the off road vehicles were not. They are too bouncy and hard to control. Going up hills is a challenge when all the car wants to do is spin around and go downhill. If you hit one slight bump wrong while going 120+ (and you will, believe me you will) you will 90% of the time lose control of the car. It takes very, very fast fingers to keep your car from hitting anything and crashing. Driving in first person (which is the only way I can drive without hitting everything [the car angle throws off my perception of how hard I'm turning]) is nearly impossible off road due to all the time your car spends with its nose way in the air from hitting something. I feel like having the game go a more realistic speed off road AND not just floor it when you try to give it gas would do wonders for the off-road specs. They did a really good job imitating the slipperiness of dirt (I grew up driving on dirt), so it should stand to reason that they should have an option, at least for when you are not racing, to accelerate like a real person would. Heck, that would be great through the whole game. Stopping and turning around is a lot harder when all your car wants to do is peel out.Fortunately, there are not a whole lot of Raid spec missions, and you don't spend a lot of time off-road. Looking past these few flaws, I love the game. It's a refreshing take on the racing genre and I can see myself easily pouring over a hundred hours into this game."
,Recommended,241560,13517566,"Posted: 22 December, 2014",all,Papa-doc,"This Game is the ultimate Racing MMO, its fun, it isn't Pay to win, it suits the casual gamer and the ""simulator"" addict, the game also gives you a small tour around america, you get to know a bit more about the country and its landscapes, cars are brutal (no ricer♥♥♥♥♥♥ the voice acting could have been better but its not bad, the only thing i found quite annoying is that, there isn't alot of ""Coop"" i never see people in the chat talking, there is a few bugs which i hope that will be fixed in a short period of time, but overall this game is just awesome, totally worth the 50€, if you like cars or racing in general, this game is for you."
