76561197970471206,Recommended,241560,13689194,"Posted: 29 December, 2014",all,Dreador,"This is a fairly good arcade-like racing game with a huge open world which keeps my interest. I enjoyed Test Drive 1 and 2 quite a bit which is what influenced me to buy The Crew. I say it's a pretty good game even though for me there are some disappointments.The biggest disappointment is there is no offline play. I can see they probably did not want hackers and such but it is still disappointing since Test Drive 1 + 2 offer offline play. If the online fuction dies then I won't be able to play without some sort of community support I guess.I like how the textures are pretty detailed compared to the Test Drive games and there are many vistas that look pretty impressive such some areas show fireworks going off , very large bridges, detailed towns and cities, airports, a space shuttle, hot air balloons and quite a bit more. Though it seems to not look very realistic since the field of view seems to make everything kind of look like toys somewhat but it is unique, clean looking, and the lighting is very well done especially at night. The dirt roads look pretty bad though compared to other games and seems like it would have been easy to fix. Though it is nice to see animals and people in the world for added detail. The in-car view does look pretty good. The camara angle changes awkwardly a bit when using nitro though.Sounds in general seem fine. I wish the car sounds were a bit fuller but aren't too bad. I do like how the sound does change when you are in the car itself.The racing is pretty fun especially since you can take shortcuts and smash through things which adds excitement. There are mini games also which allow you to win car parts which is pretty neat.For me this game is worth buying for the exploration because there are a lot of vistas, car parts, and such you can find throughout this very large map and the racing is fun too. The atmosphere of the world does feel a bit unrealistic visually but it does have it's own unique appearance which is nice. It is probably hard to be able to manage the time to create everything perfectly especially when making such a huge world."
