,Recommended,241560,14988238,"Posted: 21 March, 2015",all,JamiePhonic,"First things first, most of the poor reviews for this game are from hardcore racing game fans. this review is from the point of view of someone who has almost never played a racing game before. with that said, i can safely say that the crew is actually a pretty good game.The story is a little short with me having beat the campaign in a little under 18 hours (over the cource of about 5 days with ocasional side quests to level up my cars a bit before the next race), however the game offers some replay value in that you can go back to any mission you have done and replay it, though the rewards dont change for beating it at a higher level unless you've reached level 50 and unlocked platinum parts, in which case its worth going back and re-doing some missions.The ""skills"" are a touch annoying in that if you accidentaly trigger one while driving about you either need to open your phone and choose abort, open the map to auto abort it, or just let it time out.The game also claims to be MMO, but i played the entire campaign in solo mode because i couldnt find anyone to coop with, instead just getting an error that coop failed because there is no one in my session and in general only actually passing other players on the road a coupple of times every so often.In general, i did enjoy the story and the game as a whole and ill continue to play it to complete the challenges, skills and the factions missions you unlock after reaching new york. If you havnt played any racing games before, this is quite a good one to start with, BUT i would not reccomend buying this at full price. wait for a sale and get it then.i will say that i haven't noticed any problems with ""rubber banding AI"" or undestructable cops, but thats just me and i also haven't had the game crash on me (yet)"
