,Recommended,241560,14752032,"Posted: 5 March, 2015",all,KF690,"This game is amazing, I'm gonna do a quick pros/cons review:Pro:-Car handling is good, not enough to be called a simulator per se, but its no arcade/nfs game either.-The atmosphere and the setting is stunning, they really captured the feeling of driving through the desert, the snow, or the green fields in central USA, the cities are also amazing and expansive.-Very open ended, you can go to wherever you can see, no exceptions, almost no invisible walls, its awesome.-Traffic AI is not perfect, but the sheer amount of cars on some sections make it worth it.-Entretaining multiplayer challenges-amazing graphics-Lots of cars, very customizable-Handling reacts to the terraincons:-Bad soundtrack, very little variety. I found myself either listening to the classical music station, or simply playing some music on the background. This game urgently needs some kind of adaptive radio station to blend in with the atmosphere of each area. Driving through the appalachians? Why not some bluegrass? Driving through arizona/nevada/texas? Some country music would fit in perfectly, driving through the snow? Something more epic would probably be a nice addition. In the end, the soundtrack, which is mostly electronic music only serves if you are in a city, at night. For a game that depends so much on its atmosphere, that's a very significant negative-The story is better than TDU2, but its still lacking substance.-It gets a little repetitive, but never really ""Grindy"", for me at least.To sum it all up, it manages to capture an atmosphere similar to that of Euro Truck Simulator 2, the best moments in this game weren't spent doing some obnoxious slalom challenges in detroit, but driving calmly down the road to florida. It also feels a lot like Test drive unlimited 2, but this time there is more variety and less bugs. If you like test drive, you are surely gonna want to buy this game.Ultimately, is it worth buying?If you care about atmosphere, driving, eventually speeding and sandbox racing, YES, totally, but if you are looking for just another Y0LOSW4G 420 ULTRA FAST CAR R4C1NGE DANK SLALOM 0V3RT4KE 666, then you better stick with games that focus more on that. THIS IS AN OPEN WORLD DRIVING GAME, NOT PURE CIRCUIT RACING GAME!"
