,Recommended,241560,29610577,Posted: 31 January,all,Sleek,"Despite a pretty failed launch the game has been improved over time and now the driving physics are actually decent.However, getting air and other ""bumpy"" actions tends to still be very flawed and unpredictable.The car selection has become quite good and the attention to detail on them is pretty good as well. Customizability is one of the better ones of racing games though the liveries cannot be custom made.The storyline is decent though rather cliche at times. Some missions are pretty infuriating while others are a walk in the park.The main downfall is there are still quite a few bugs and multiplayer matchmaking only works sometimes. I often end up spending either a few minutes to find a crew to do the crew challenge at Summit events or more often than not the matchmaker never seems to find someone else for even hours. Physics when on rough terrain (Raid and Monster Trucks usually) tend to be very unpredictable and frustrating.Another flaw is there is basically no competitive reason to turn off assists and use manual gear shifting as even when manual the cars shift rather slow. There may be a slight advantage to using sport mode instead of full assits though its only minor as the steering assist sometimes does drive a player off course and that is reduced in sport. Contrary to most other driving games there is no acceleration penalty when using full assistance and automatic gearing."
