76561198071704334,Not Recommended,241560,24040412,"Posted: 3 July, 2016",all,Coldhawk,"The Crew is a love/hate relationship. The gameplay is good enough, the cars are beautiful, the graphics are great but the developers are insane. If you've read other reviews you know why I dislike them. If you haven't:The Crew launched back at 2014 with massive hype leading up to it. It supposedly had the map of the entire USA, hundreds of cars and the bestest multiplayer. At launch it costed 60€ and the season pass at 25€. After turning out to be a letdown, the game still had a community and the developers were still developing. So 2015 comes and The Wild Run is released which adds a graphical overhaul, new weather effects and The Summit. Also, new cars were added every month with each new summit which was nice.  The Wild Run was a nice feature to have and was welcomed. For The price it was good with me. Now, we get to the juicy part. Calling All Units. That currently costs 25€ and adds a new gamemode and 11 skins for old cars. Now the problem is that if you bought the 25€ season pass you didn't get Wild Run or Calling All Units. And if you had The Wild Run you didn't get Calling All Units. But if you buy Calling All units you do get The Wild Run. So Ivory Tower or Ubisoft or whoever, is making old fans and players pay for new and useless stuff while new players get everything."
