76561198352171100,Recommended,241560,34473046,Posted: 24 August,all,2000.ats,"Pros:Amazing map. Throughout detailed and extremely large.Decent selection of carsBroad customizationUpgrade system (you actually have to play the game to make your car fast)Decent graphics (I've found that anti aliasing can kill fps if you don't have a ton of VRAM)Best story I've seen in a racing gameI got about 20-25 hours of playing just the storyMost of the glitches (cutscenes in particular) are super fun to mess withCons: (big breath)Graphics can look like crap in some places (crank up that demanding anti aliasing)Most of the cool cars are dlc or extremely expensiveVery hard to get money (I'm talking 1k-2k each race)The physics are really wierd at slow speeds (but they do get better as you start getting into faster cars that can handle the speed)Sometimes the map feels TOO big, like when you have to do a long road trip and it takes you half an hour to an hour at 200 MPH on highway to cross the mapThe physics (yes I'm mentioning them again), while they eventually start to make sense and become intuitive, are EXTREMELY difficult to completely understandConnection issues with multiplayerTHE GAME IS ONLINE ONLY SO IF YOUR PC IS IN A CRAPPY SPOT OF THE HOUSE WHERE THERE IS NO CONNECTION GOOD LUCK PLAYING THIS GAME (fr tho)Overall, I loved the game, even though it has ALOT of quirks. The vast amount of places to visit and things to do really make up for the faults that this game has. The physics can be wonky, but make almost perfect sense in faster cars at high speeds. The only thing that drives me nuts is how hard it is to get money in this game. This is NOT Forza Horizon 3 where they throw money at you constantly, AT ALL. It is hard to get the fast cars because of this but not impossible.So, in short:Physics take a while to masterGame is absolutely massiveDecent length storyDifficult to get moneyBasically, if you've got alot of TIME to play, then get this game. But if you can only hope on every Saturday or something, go find something that doesn't need you in it for the long haul."
