,Recommended,241560,33885866,Posted: 29 July,all,Frogster,"I played through the story missions by now, while also doing side missions, customizing my cars etc. and i can easily say that this game is worth the 12eur i paid for it on sale. 30euros though... Hmm i don't know.If you are looking for a solid car game with a slightly arcadey feel, a huge map, car customization and nice graphics this is something for you.Pros:- Nice graphics- Ran nice and smooth on GTX 970- Nice controls (controller recommended)- 30+ hours story missions- 30+ hours worth of side quests and pvp missions etc.- Loads of customization for cars- The ability to tune your favorite car into an offroad beast or circut racer etc.- A nice variety of cars in the base game (I have not bought any of the DLC as of writing this)- Huge map with loads of different terrains and big areas to explore and have fun with your friends in.Cons:- Uplay... obviously- Had a few crashes here and there, but rare.- I wasn't personally annoyed by this but the game is always online with other players.- Too many DLCs- Little bit expensive if not on sale- Soundtrack not quite big enough. After playing a for a few hours you begin to hear the same songs again.In summary i definately think that this game is a solid racing game for those who would like a pretty, nicely controlled racing game with loads of car customization and a huge map.I give the base game with no DLC a 7,5/10"
